Three students of the Greenfield University in Kaduna State who were abducted by bandits on Tuesday night have been killed by their abductors. During the attack on the private university along the Kaduna- Abuja highway, a staff member of the school was also killed. SaharaReporters Media The Kaduna State Commissioner for internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, who confirmed the sad news, said the remains of three students were found on Friday in Kwanan Bature village, a place close to the university. He said their remains had been taken to a mortuary by the Force Commander, Operation Thunder Strike, Lieutenant Colonel MH Abdullahi and him. However, the number of students kidnapped at the school is still unknown.Â 



